SECTION 7: M* TRANSFORM -- COMPLETE FORMAL DEFINITION
--------------------------------------------------

  M*(S) = lim(eps->0) [log N_4(eps) / log N_2(eps)] * (c/S_max) * I_600[R]
                              ^------ D4/D2 ------^

  Where:
  S       -- integer token sequence (Gematria stream)
  D_4     -- 4D Hausdorff dimension from box-count N_4(eps)
  D_2     -- 2D Hausdorff dimension from box-count N_2(eps)
  c       -- alpha_0 = 299 + pi/10 (scaling shaft, M1)
  S_max   -- 400  (T-22 token ceiling, normalisation)
  R       -- [D_3/D_2, D_4/D_2]  (ratio vector)
  I_600   -- 600-cell indicator: 1 if R in [phi, 15/8] within 3%

  CLIFF CORRECTION at k_c=3.183 (certified M19):
  Off-cliff: append (dC/dk)^(-1/5) as damping factor
  At-cliff:  exponent inverts to +1/5 (derivative fixed point)

  FINAL CERTIFIED FORM (at cliff):
  M*(S) = (D4/D2) * (c/S_max) * (dC/dk)^(+1/5) * I_600[R]
  M*_ratio = M*(S) / H4_base    [H4_base = 120/11]

  TARGET: M*_ratio = 12/11 = 1.09090909...

